<div class="span12">
	<h3 class="underline">About</h3>
        <p>French Institute of Bioinformatics Journal is a collection of articles and their demonstrations,for <i>Biological analysis</i> with <a href="http://www.france-bioinformatique.fr/en">French Institute of Bioinformatics</a> </p>

        <p>The French Institute of Bioinformatics (referred to as IFB hereafter) is a national service infrastructure in bioinformatics that was created following the call for proposals, “National Infrastructures in Biology and Health”, of the “Investments for the Future” initiative (ANR-11-INBS-0013).</p>

	<p>This project gathers together the bioinformatics platforms of the main French research organizations, <a href="http://www.cnrs.fr/">CNRS</a>, <a href="http://www.inra.fr/">INRA</a>, <a href="http://www.inria.fr/">INRIA</a>, <a href="http://ceasciences.fr/en/index.php">CEA</a> and <a href="http://www.inserm.fr/">INSERM</a> as well as <a href="http://www.cirad.fr/">CIRAD</a> the <a href="http://www.pasteur.fr/fr">Pasteur</a> and <a href="http://curie.fr/">Cuire</a>, and the French universities. There are currently 30 <a href="http://www.france-bioinformatique.fr/?q=en/platforms">platforms</a> grouped into six regional centers that span the whole of France.</p>
       
        <p>IFB's principal mission is to provide basic <a href="http://www.france-bioinformatique.fr/?q=en/services">services</a> and resources in bioinformatics for scientists and engineers working in the life sciences.</p>

	<p>If you'd like to <b>suggest improvements</b> to the site (anything!) please contacte us. We'll do our best to fix any bugs right away, or to consider adding new features. If you prefer to contact us by email, please write us at <a href="mailto:contact@groupes.france-bioinformatique.fr ">contact@groupes.france-bioinformatique.fr </a>.</p>
</div>
